{"parse":{"title":"The Theological Method of Samkara","pageid":34610257,"revid":805719786,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Orphan\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"display: none\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wiki letter w.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/60px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/80px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"44\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Orphan\" title=\"Wikipedia:Orphan\">orphan</a>, as no other articles <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere&amp;target=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara&amp;namespace=0\">link to it</a></b>. Please <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Link\" title=\"Help:Link\">introduce links</a> to this page from <span class=\"plainlinks\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3ASearch&amp;redirs=1&amp;search=The+Theological+Method+of+Samkara&amp;fulltext=Search&amp;ns0=1&amp;title=Special%3ASearch&amp;advanced=1&amp;fulltext=The+Theological+Method+of+Samkara\">related articles</a></span>; try the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//edwardbetts.com/find_link?q=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara\">Find link tool</a> for suggestions.  <small><i>(August 2012)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>The Theological Method of Samkara</b> is <a href=\"/wiki/Richard_De_Smet\" title=\"Richard De Smet\">Richard De Smet</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/Doctoral_dissertation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Doctoral dissertation\">doctoral dissertation</a>, defended at the <a href=\"/wiki/Pontifical_Gregorian_University\" title=\"Pontifical Gregorian University\">Pontifical Gregorian University</a>, Rome, in 1953, with Fr Renatus Arnou, SJ as director. The dissertation, which rapidly became well-known, remains unpublished<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\"><span title=\"The text near this tag may need clarification or removal of jargon. (October 2017)\">clarification needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>. The dissertation proposed that <a href=\"/wiki/Sankaracarya\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sankaracarya\">Sankara</a> was not so much a pure philosopher, but rather a <i>srutivadin</i> or theologian, an exegete or hermeneutician of the scriptures. It also proposed that the doctrine of indirect signification (<i>lak\u1e63a\u1e47\u0101</i>) plays a central role in Sankara's theological method.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> However, in the dissertation itself, De Smet does not arrive clearly at his later rejection of the classical illusionist (<i>mayavadin</i>) monistic interpretation of Sankara in favour of a non-dualist 'realist' one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publication\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publication</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>De Smet himself reports that he sent the dissertation to various specialists in 1954, people like <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Olivier_Lacombe&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Olivier Lacombe (page does not exist)\">Olivier Lacombe</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hajime_Nakamura\" title=\"Hajime Nakamura\">Hajime Nakamura</a>, S.K. Belvalkar, Dhirendra Mohan Datta, Paul Hacker, <a href=\"/wiki/Helmuth_von_Glasenapp\" title=\"Helmuth von Glasenapp\">Helmuth von Glasenapp</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Pierre_Johanns\" title=\"Pierre Johanns\">Pierre Johanns</a>, A.J. Alston, <a href=\"/wiki/Louis_Renou\" title=\"Louis Renou\">Louis Renou</a>, A.C. Mukerji, Daniel Ingalls, Jacques-Albert Cuttat, <a href=\"/wiki/Hubert_Olympus_Mascarenhas\" title=\"Hubert Olympus Mascarenhas\">H.O. Mascarenhas</a> and J.B. van Buitenen, who seem to have appraised it positively.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While De Smet's thesis has not been completely accepted among Indologists in general and among specialists of Sankara, it has received a positive reception by K. Satchidananda Murty in his <i>Revelation and Reason in Advaita</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and by Anantanand Rambachan in his <i>Accomplishing the Accomplished: The Vedas as a Source of Valid Knowledge in Sankara</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publication\">Publication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Publication\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In one of his last letters, De Smet had given permission for the publication of an updated and edited version of his thesis to George McLean, who worked with Bradley J. Malkovsky towards this end.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> In his introduction to the De Smet commemorative volume, Malkovsky indicates that publication is in process.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The publication is still awaited.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Richard_De_Smet\" title=\"Richard De Smet\">De Smet, Richard</a>. <i>The Theological Method of Samkara.</i> Pontifical Gregorian University, Rome, 1953 (unpublished).</li>\n<li>Murty, K. Satchidananda. <i>Revelation and Reason in Advaita.</i> Waltair: Andhra University Press, 1959; reprint Delhi: Motilal Banarsidass, 1974.</li>\n<li>Rambachan, A. <i>Accomplishing the Accomplished: The Veda as a Source of Valid Knowledge in \u015aa\u1e45kara</i>. Honululu: University of Hawaii Press, 1991.</li>\n<li>Malkovsky, Bradley J. \u201cIntroduction: The Life and Work of Richard V. De Smet, S.J.\u201d <i>New Perspectives on Advaita Ved\u0101nta: Essays in Commemoration of Professor Richard De Smet, S.J.</i> Ed. Bradley J. Malkovsky. Leiden / Boston / K\u00f6ln: Brill, 2000.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Francis_Xavier_Clooney\" title=\"Francis Xavier Clooney\">Clooney, F.X.</a> <i>Theology after Ved\u0101nta: An Experiment in Comparative Theology.</i> Albany: State University of New York Press, 1993. Delhi: Sri Satguru Publications, 1993.</li>\n<li>Coelho, Ivo. \"Introduction.\" <i>Understanding Sankara: Essays by Richard De Smet.</i> Ed. Ivo Coelho. Delhi: Motilal Banarsidass, forthcoming. 1-30.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Theological_Method_of_Samkara&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">De Smet, 'The Theological Method of Samkara' 290, 292.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">I. Coelho, \"Introduction,\" <i>Understanding Sankara: Essays by Richard De Smet,</i> ed. Ivo Coelho (Delhi: Motilal Banarsidass, forthcoming) 4-7.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">R. De Smet, \"From the Vedas to Radhakrishnan,\" <i>Understanding Sankara: Essays by Richard De Smet</i> ch. 19, p. 295.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">(Waltair: Andhra University Press, 1959; reprint Delhi: Motilal Banarsidass, 1974).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">(Honululu: University of Hawaii Press, 1991). For a comment on these two authors, see De Smet, \"From Catholic Theology to Sankara Vedanta and Return with Fr F.X. Clooney,\" <i>Understanding Sankara: Essays by Richard De Smet</i> 411.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ivo Coelho, \"Introduction,\" <i>Understanding Sankara: Essays by Richard De Smet,</i> 25, note 4.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Malkovsky 8, note 11.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2235\nCached time: 20180922075347\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: true\nCPU time usage: 0.108 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.139 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 325/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 6470/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 499/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 11/40\nExpensive parser function count: 2/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 2356/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.041/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.24 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  103.135      1 -total\n 58.86%   60.707      1 Template:Orphan\n 41.01%   42.298      1 Template:What\n 40.13%   41.393      1 Template:Ambox\n 35.52%   36.636      1 Template:Fix-span\n 20.39%   21.029      1 Template:Replace\n 13.66%   14.089      1 Template:Delink\n 10.81%   11.152      2 Template:Category_handler\n  4.30%    4.435      1 Template:Fix/category\n  2.04%    2.107      1 Te